<h1>Creatrix Tiara</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://creatrixtiara.com/now">creatrixtiara.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Johor Bahru

Malaysia
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I'm currently looking for work. My background is in arts, media, education, tech, and social justice.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I sign up for anything that looks interesting!
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Signing up for anything that looks interesting leads me to fun, enriching experiences that help me grow while also giving me space to contribute and share with others. Through that philosophy, I've become an international performance artist and writer, met other tech-based changemakers, worked with youth and students on arts education projects, and became heavily involved with major feminist, anti-racist, and pro-LGBTQ causes.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
I read this essay about Genevieve Lim where she talks about how writers of color get dismissed so it feels like their work doesn't matter...but because their work "doesn't matter", they're free to do whatever they want.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Bengali Harlem and the Lost Histories of South Asian America by Vivek Bald
</p>

